The SCC and the SWWC have implemented safety precautions to prevent and mitigate a chlorine release. These include maintenance, training, operational procedures and inspection procedures, as well as an Emergency Action Plan in the event of a release.

The Shelby County Commission Management and the SWWC are committed to:

(1) Preventing accidents;
(2) Training employees in the correct response procedures in the event of an accident;
(3) Providing leadership to the community with respect to emergency preparedness;
(4) Addressing citizen concerns by fully explaining potential hazards associated with facility operations and all steps being taken to prevent and mitigate accidents; and
(5) Being good governmental and corporate citizens of Shelby County.

This Risk Management Plan provides information on how the SCC and SWWC intent to manage the risks associated with the chlorine disinfection process used at the SWTP, but more importantly stresses the commitment to ensuring a safe environment for employees, visitors and the community.
